comments.body: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1rTlddMH5-yZKpFK2FYb36rqvdnqiwbNDbuqjoe1thdQ/edit?usp=sharing has been cleaned and prepared for export into the TSV required for loading into the QA environment.

While this is being loaded into the QA environment and reindexed, I have discovered the following: https://github.com/pulibrary/dspace-development/issues/806. I shall address this as a high priority issue and ensure that this is resolved immediately.
Aside from the X.509 certificate, the import seems to have been successful:
There are some anomalous entries which must be removed manually by executing commands directly to the database server.

The entries were successfully removed, and the QA sheet was successfully reimported. However, when attempting to reindex, the following error was logged:

Manually removing the corrupted Lucene index files, and then restarting the server, followed by reindexing, ensured that only the valid QA entries were properly imported.
It was also necessary to once more reimport the QA submission records in order to ensure that the e-mail addresses follow the pattern `thesis.central.pu+[NET_ID]@gmail.com`.
I have also confirmed that the account for Lynn Durgin has administrative privileges.
Lynn has been notified by e-mail of the status of the QA deployment, and I have requested that this now be tested when she is next available.

tiger-data-app.title: [Honeybadger] @project should not be `nil` within the TigerdataMailer Class

comments.body:
Two possible approaches to this might be the following:

```ruby
class TigerdataMailer < ApplicationMailer
  def project_creation
    config = Rails.application.config.tigerdata_mail[:project_creation]

    if !params.key?(:project)
      Rails.logger.error("Failed to resolve the project using ID #{params[:project]} within #{self.class}")
      return
    end

    @project = params[:project]
    filebase = @project.metadata[:project_id].tr("/", "_")
```

Or:

```ruby
class TigerdataMailer < ApplicationMailer
  def project_creation
    config = Rails.application.config.tigerdata_mail[:project_creation]
    @project = params[:project]
    raise(ArgumentError, "Failed to resolve the project using ID #{params[:project]} within #{self.class}") if @project.nil?

    filebase = @project.metadata[:project_id].tr("/", "_")
```
